Program no-03
Experiment name:Implementation of stack

AIM:
To implement a program for Stack operations (Push and Pop) using an array in C.

ALOGORITHM:
1.Start the program.
2.Declare variables: MAX, item, top = -1, choice = 0.
3.Ask the user to enter the size of the stack (MAX).
4.Create an integer array STACK[MAX].
5.Repeat the following steps until the user chooses Exit (choice = 3):
6.Display the menu:
Push
Pop
Exit
7.Read the user’s choice.
If choice = 1 (Push):
   Check if top == MAX - 1.
     If true, display “Stack Overflow”.
     Else, read the element to push, increment top and insert the element in STACK[top].
If choice = 2 (Pop):
 Check if top == -1.
 If true, display “Stack Underflow”.
 Else, display the popped element, then decrement top.
If choice = 3 (Exit):
  Terminate the program.
Otherwise:
 Display “Incorrect choice”.
6.Stop the program.

PROGRAM:
#include <stdio.h>
int main()
{
    int MAX, item;
    int top = -1;
    int choice = 0;

    printf("Enter the stack: ");
    scanf("%d", &MAX);
    int STACK[MAX];

    while (choice != 3)
    {
        printf("\n1. Push\n2. Pop\n3. Exit\n");
        printf("Enter your choice: ");
        scanf("%d", &choice);

        switch (choice)
        {
        case 1:
            if (top == MAX - 1)
            {
                printf("Stack overflow\n");
            }
            else
            {
                printf("Enter the value to push: ");
                scanf("%d", &item);
                top = top + 1;
                STACK[top] = item;
            }
            break;

        case 2:
            if (top == -1)
            {
                printf("Stack is underflow\n");
            }
            else
            {
                item = STACK[top];
                top = top - 1;
                printf("Popped element is: %d\n", item);
            }
            break;

        case 3:
            return 0;

        default:
            printf("Incorrect choice\n");
            break;
        }
    }
}

OUTPUT:
Enter the stack: 3

1. Push
2. Pop
3. Exit
Enter your choice: 1
Enter the value to push: 53

1. Push
2. Pop
3. Exit
Enter your choice: 1
Enter the value to push: 45

1. Push
2. Pop
3. Exit
Enter your choice: 2
Popped element is: 45

1. Push
2. Pop
3. Exit
Enter your choice: 3

Result:
The program for implementation of Stack using array was successfully executed.
It performs Push and Pop operations correctly based on user choice. 
